<div dir="ltr"><div><div>Hi Angelos,<br></div>PostgreSQL is definitely on the roadmap. We have partial support for it: database migrations should work but we haven&#39;t tested all the backend queries against it. However its not a high priority until we&#39;ve got a complete working UI.<br><br></div>Cheers,<br>Robbie.<br><div><div><div><div><div><div class="gmail_extra"><br><div class="gmail_quote">On Fri, Jan 30, 2015 at 11:54 AM, Angelos Tzotsos <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:gcpp.kalxas@..." target="_blank">gcpp.kalxas@...</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex">Hi all,<br>
<br>
I would like to ask if your upcoming version 3.0 is going to support PostgreSQL or SQLite as potential back-ends.<br>
We (OSGeoLive project) would like to use PostgreSQL instead of MySQL to demonstrate Ushahidi in our next release (9.0 in August).<br>
Any chance this feature could be added on your roadmap?<br>
<br>
Best,<br>
Angelos<span class=""><br>
